Comments.Body:
https://lume.land/plugins/tailwindcss/ need to be updated.

Now the syntax to use Tailwind is:

```
@import "tailwindcss";
```

The importer is defined by Lume in order to resolve the includes to `_includes` folder and be able to load remote files or files created dynamically during the build process.

I'm thinking of an option to map some routes, for example:

```js
site.use(sass({
  includes: {
    "uswds": "./path-to-uswds",
    "uswds-theme": "./path-to-uswds-theme"
  }
});
```

Would this work for you?

Ok, probably a includes map is not a good idea, because the pkg loader can use patterns, so you have to map a lot of files.
Do you know if the uswds package has a custom package loader? Maybe there's a way to combine Lume loader with other custom loaders.

If you want to try some options on your own.

- Copy [the sass plugin file](https://github.com/lumeland/lume/blob/60892e9551bb2936d3d1637f43d8c5e04c42644c/plugins/sass.ts#L73) to your local. For example, to `_plugins/sass.ts`
- In the `deno.json` file, change the import maps to use your local copy:
```jsonc
{
  "imports": {
    // ...
    "https://deno.land/x/lume@v2.5.1/plugins/sass.ts": "./_plugins/sass.ts"
  }
}
```

Now you can modify your copy, like moving `...options.option` to the last, or try to register more than one importer (since it [accepts an array](https://sass-lang.com/documentation/js-api/interfaces/options/#importers).

Let me know if you find a solution, and I will include it in the next Lume version.

@tdillon I just updated the Sass plugin to allow additional importers.
Before this change, if Lume importer didn't find any file, a error is thrown.
I just remove this part and now it returns `null`, so additional importers should work. Commit: https://github.com/lumeland/lume/commit/c8aff5475efeb2a20b43cde24dda0e9c94cf96f8

Now you can specify additional load paths:

```js
site.use(sass({
  options: {
    loadPaths: ["./node_modules/@uswds/uswds/packages"],
  }
}));
```

Or other importers:

```js
site.use(sass({
  options: {
    importers: [new NodePackageImporter()]
  }
}));
```

To test it, you have to upgrade Lume to the latest development version with `deno task lume upgrade --dev`.
Let me know if this works for you.

Regarding Node Package Importer, I cannot get [SASS built-in modules](https://sass-lang.com/documentation/modules/) to work.

An example like this
```scss
@use 'sass:color";

:root {
  --var-a: color.scale("#ffffff", $red: 50%);
}
```

will render
```css
:root {
  --var-a: color.scale("#ffffff", $red: 50%)
}
```

These built-in modules are defined in the core dart-sass package, written in Dart (compiled to Javascript), so changing `loadPaths` and `importers` options won't help.

Right. The result is the same with running `sass` command directly on a sample file. 

It works with interpolation though, so:
```scss
@use "sass:color";

:root {
  --var-a: #{color.scale("#123456", $red: 15%)};
}
```
produces the correct result. Yes, CSS custom properties [are treated differently](https://sass-lang.com/documentation/style-rules/declarations/#custom-properties).

Sorry for the misleading report!

