Lume filters are passed in the second argument. You can use the `md` filter to render markdown:

```js
export default function ({ title }, helpers) {
  const rendered = helpers.md(title);
}
```

[More info about `md` filter](https://lume.land/plugins/markdown/#md-filter).

FYI, there's the [plaintext](https://lume.land/plugins/plaintext/) plugin to register a filter to remove html and markdown syntax.

Helpers are provided by Lume in the second argument of the component function (read my previous comment).
In your case:

```js
export default function (props: {
  title: string;
  sidebar: Sidebar_;
  url: string;
  sectionTitle: string;
  sectionHref: string;
}, helpers: Lume.Helpers) {
  const renderedTitle = helpers.md(title);
  // code
}
```

