The plugin is very simple: https://github.com/lumeland/lume/blob/master/plugins/bundler.js

It only configures your site to load js and ts files as assets and then register a processor to tranform the content of these files using `Deno.bundle()`. It's an experimental plugin, I'm agree that `deno bundle` is not mature enough.

You don't need this plugin for this, because, as you can see, it's very simple. Plugins are just simple intefaces to configure your site, but you don't need them to register new loaders, processors, etc. In your `_config.js` file you can do the following:

```js
