Lume components are rendered in building time, they are not intended for client side. You can include client-side CSS and JS code in the components but using the `css` and `js` named exports. For example:

```ts
// CSS code
export const css = `
button {
  background-color: blue;
}
`;

// Client side JavaScript code
export const js = `
function clickButton() {
    alert("You've clicked me!");
}
`;

// Component to render on building:
export default function () {
  return <button onclick="clickButton()">Click me</button>
}
```

This can be useful for web components or simple use cases.
If you need to ship more client side javascript, you can use the [esbuild plugin](https://lume.land/plugins/esbuild/) that can compile JS(X) and TS(X).

Take a look to the [react-todo demo](https://github.com/lumeland/react-todo) for a more advanced example, it's a web application built with React, pre-rendered in building time and hydrated in client side.

You can use a middleware to setup CORS headers. Middlewares in Lume are just functions with the following signature:

```ts
type Handler = (request: Request) => Promise<Response>;

async function middleware (request: Request, next: Handler): Promise<Response> {
  return await next(request);
});
```

Packages by [httpland](https://github.com/httpland) use the same signature for middlewares so probably you can use their [cors_protocol](https://deno.land/x/cors_protocol@1.0.0-beta.6) module as following (I didn't try it):

```ts
import { withCors } from "https://deno.land/x/cors_protocol@$VERSION/mod.ts";

async function corsMiddleware(request, next) {
    const response = await next(request);
    return withCors(request, response);
}
```

To use this middleware in the local server (with `deno task lume -s`), just [add it in your _config.ts file](https://lume.land/docs/configuration/config-file/#middlewares):

```ts
import lume from "lume/mod.ts";
import cors from "./_middlewares/cors.ts";

const site = lume({
  server: {
    middlewares: [cors]
  }
});

export default site;
```

