- <img src="/img/2021-06-01-jordgubbar.jpg" alt="jordgubbar" imagick="avif webp 600@1,1.5,2">
```

Another option is using the resolve_urls plugin, but it must be used before the picture plugin (I guess this is the reason it didn't work to you).

```js
import lume from "lume/mod.ts";
import picture from "lume/plugins/picture.ts";
import imagick from "lume/plugins/imagick.ts";
import resolve_urls from "lume/plugins/resolve_urls.ts";

const site = lume();

site.use(resolve_urls());
site.use(picture());
site.use(imagick());

export default site;
```

This plugin automatically detects and fixes the urls, so the `picture` plugin can work with the final name.

